\left|\zeta\left(\sigma+it\right)\right|^{2}=\zeta\left(\sigma+it\right)\overline{\zeta\left(\sigma+it\right)}=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\left(mn\right)^{-\sigma}n^{-it}m^{it}.
\int_{-T}^{T}n^{-it}m^{it}dt=\int_{-T}^{T}\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)^{it}dt=\frac{i\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)^{-iT}-i\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)^{iT}}{\log\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)}.
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\sum_{m\neq n}\left(mn\right)^{-\sigma}\frac{i\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)^{-iT}-i\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)^{iT}}{\log\left(\frac{m}{n}\right)}
\lim_{T\rightarrow \infty} \frac{1}{2T}\int_{-T}^{T}\left|\zeta\left(\sigma+it\right)\right|^{2}dt=\sum_{n=m}\left(mn\right)^{-\sigma}=\sum_{n=1}^\infty (n^2)^{-\sigma}=\zeta(2\sigma).
